label.value: mechanosensory neuron of mechanosensory ventral double row bristle

value.value: Neuron involved in mechanosensation innervating a mechanosensory ventral double row bristle.

label.value: L3 nerve

value.value: Nerve bundle running through wing vein L3.

label.value: campaniform sensillum anterior crossvein neuron

value.value: Neuron associated with the wing anterior crossvein sensillum (Murray et al., 1984).

label.value: E-1 neuron

value.value: Neuron that has its soma near that of the anterior crossvein campaniform sensillum neuron and its axon feeding into the L3 nerve (Murray et al., 1984). It does not possess a typical dendrite with a conspicuous distal tip and does not seem to associate with the surface of the epithelium (Murray et al., 1984).

label.value: campaniform sensillum dorsal humeral crossvein neuron

value.value: Neuron innervating the dorsal humeral crossvein campaniform sensillum.

definition.value: Along with the ventral humeral crossvein campaniform sensillum neuron, this neuron pioneers the proximal two thirds of the costal nerve path (Murray et al., 1984).

label.value: costal nerve

value.value: Nerve that travels through the medial costal vein of the proximal anterior wing margin (Palka et al., 1979), it remains distinct from the combined L1-L3 nerve until both nerves leave the wing via the anterior dorsal mesothoracic nerve (Murray et al., 1984). It is composed of axons collected from the marginal sensilla of the distal, medial and proximal costa, as well as the tegula (Palka et al., 1979).

label.value: campaniform sensillum ventral humeral crossvein neuron

value.value: Neuron innervating the ventral humeral crossvein campaniform sensillum.

definition.value: Along with the dorsal humeral crossvein campaniform sensillum neuron, this neuron pioneers the proximal two thirds of the costal nerve path (Murray et al., 1984).

label.value: campaniform sensillum L3-v of wing vein L3 neuron

value.value: Neuron innervating the ventral sensillum of wing vein L3.

label.value: campaniform sensillum L3-1 of wing vein L3 neuron

value.value: Neuron innervating the L3-1 campaniform sensillum of wing vein L3.

label.value: campaniform sensillum L3-2 of wing vein L3 neuron

value.value: Neuron innervating the second, medially located campaniform sensillum of wing vein L3.

label.value: campaniform sensillum L3-3 of wing vein L3 neuron

value.value: Neuron innervating the campaniform sensillum L3-3 of wing vein L3.

label.value: E-2 neuron

value.value: Neuron that has its soma near that of the campaniform sensillum L3-2 of wing vein L3 neuron and its axon feeding into the L3 nerve (Murray et al., 1984). It does not possess a typical dendrite with a conspicuous distal tip and does not seem to associate with the surface of the epithelium (Murray et al., 1984).

label.value: E-T neuron

value.value: Neuron that has its soma near those of the neurons innervating the twin sensilla of the margin and its axon feeding into the marginal nerve (Murray et al., 1984). It does not possess a typical dendrite with a conspicuous distal tip and does not seem to associate with the surface of the epithelium (Murray et al., 1984).

label.value: chemosensory sensillum of the female genitalia

value.value: Any sensillum (FBbt:00007152) that is part of some female genitalia (FBbt:00004827) and is capable of some detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception (GO:0050907).

definition.value: Short trichoid sensilla of hypogynium might be chemosensory, as they are multiply innervated (Taylor, 1989).

label.value: mesothoracic leg taste bristle chemosensory neuron

value.value: Gustatory neuron innervating a mesothoracic leg taste bristle. There are between 2 and 4 per bristle (Stocker, 1994).

label.value: mesothoracic leg taste bristle mechanosensory neuron

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a mesothoracic leg taste bristle. Each bristle is singly innervated by a mechanosensory neuron (Stocker, 1994).

label.value: metathoracic leg taste bristle chemosensory neuron

value.value: Gustatory neuron innervating a metathoracic leg taste bristle. There are between 2 and 4 per bristle (Stocker, 1994).

label.value: metathoracic leg taste bristle mechanosensory neuron

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a metathoracic leg taste bristle. Each bristle is singly innervated by a mechanosensory neuron (Stocker, 1994).

label.value: prothoracic leg taste bristle chemosensory neuron

value.value: Gustatory neuron innervating a prothoracic leg taste bristle. There are between 2 and 4 per bristle (Stocker, 1994).

label.value: prothoracic leg taste bristle mechanosensory neuron

value.value: Mechanosensory neuron innervating a prothoracic leg taste bristle. Each bristle is singly innervated by a mechanosensory neuron (Stocker, 1994).

label.value: larval gnathal ganglion

value.value: Region of the embryonic/larval central nervous system consisting of the neuromeres of the three gnathal segments; mandibular, maxillary and labial (Hartenstein et al., 2018). Compared to thoracic and abdominal neuromeres, the number and size of primary lineages are decreased in the labial neuromere, and decrease further in each successive anterior gnathal neuromere (Rickert et al., 2018). It is found in the subesophageal zone, between the tritocerebrum and the prothoracic neuromere (Hartenstein et al., 2018). It separates from the prothoracic neuromere during metamorphosis (Kendroud et al., 2018).

label.value: embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion area 1

value.value: Chemosensory neuron target area located at the midline of the larval subesophageal ganglion (SOG). This area receives input from pharyngeal chemosensory neurons (the dorsal pharyngeal sense organ, the dorsal pharyngeal organ, and the posterior pharyngeal sense organ) (Colomb et al., 2007).

label.value: embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion area 2

value.value: Large chemosensory target area located adjacent to area 1 of the larval subesophageal ganglion. This region receives input from the dorsal pharyngeal sense organ, the ventral pharyngeal sense organ, the posterior pharyngeal sense organ, the dorsal pharyngeal organ, the terminal organ, and the ventral pharyngeal sense organ (Colomb et al., 2007).

label.value: embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion area 3

value.value: Small chemosensory target area located laterally in the larval subesophageal ganglion. This region receives input from non-olfactory neurons of the dorsal organ and from thoracic projections originating in the Kolbchen (also called the 'ventral pit'; Colomb et al., 2007).

label.value: embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion area 4

value.value: Large chemosensory target area of the larval subesophageal ganglion, located adjacent to the antennal lobes. One or a few neurites from dorsal pharyngeal sense organ neuron(s), and an atypical dorsal organ neuron whose dendrites extend into the terminal organ, target this region (Colomb et al., 2007).

label.value: gustatory receptor neuron of terminal organ dorsolateral group

value.value: Gustatory receptor neuron whose dendrites innervate the terminal organ on the surface of the larval head, but whose soma is located in the dorsal organ ganglion (Python and Stocker, 2002). The axons of these neurons project via the antennal nerve (Python and Stocker, 2002) into area 4 of the subesophageal ganglion (Colomb et al., 2007). There are 3 of these neurons on each side, and all have a dendrite in the dorsomedial papilla of the terminal organ dorsolateral group (Rist and Thum, 2017).

label.value: gustatory receptor neuron of terminal organ

value.value: Gustatory receptor neuron associated with the terminal organ on the surface of the larval head. There is around 23 of these neurons, 3 in the dorso-lateral terminal organ group and 21 in the distal group.

label.value: gustatory receptor neuron of the dorsal organ

value.value: Gustatory receptor neuron that has its cell body in the dorsal organ ganglion and innervates the dorsal organ on the surface of the larval head (Python and Stocker, 2002). Its axon projects via the antennal nerve (Python and Stocker, 2002). Two of these cells per dorsal organ express Gr2a and Gr28a (Kwon et al., 2011). Projections from at least some of these neurons innervate subesophageal ganglion area 3 (Colomb et al., 2007).

definition.value: DO has 11 sensory neurons in the base region (peripheral to the dome), which are mainly thought to be thermo-/mechano-sensory (Komarov and Sprecher, 2022 - FBrf0251522). The most likely two candidates for gustatory sensilla lack a terminal pore in the L1, so Richter et al. (2024) (doi:10.7554/eLife.91155.2) question whether the Gr2a/Gr28a neurons are gustatory.

label.value: gustatory receptor neuron of the ventral organ

value.value: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the ventral organ on the surface of the larval head.

label.value: larval gustatory receptor neuron of the dorsal pharyngeal sense organ

value.value: Gustatory receptor that innervates the larval dorsal pharyngeal sense organ.

label.value: larval gustatory receptor neuron of the ventral pharyngeal sense organ

value.value: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the larval ventral pharyngeal sense organ.

label.value: larval gustatory receptor neuron of the posterior pharyngeal sense organ

value.value: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the larval posterior pharyngeal sense organ.

label.value: mechanosensory medial triple row bristle

value.value: Stout, singly-innervated mechanosensory bristle of the medial row of triple row wing sensilla (Hartenstein and Posakony, 1989).

definition.value: This bristle type is believed to be mechanosensory based on the presence of a characteristic microtubular body present in the single innervating neuron (Palka et al., 1979).

label.value: dorsal double row bristle

value.value: Any chaeta (FBbt:00005177) that is part of some dorsal row of double row of wing sensilla (FBbt:00004332).

label.value: row

value.value: Anatomical group whose component structures are arranged in a row.

label.value: sensillum row

value.value: A row of sensilla.

label.value: array of rows

value.value: Multiple parallel rows.

label.value: array of sensillum rows

value.value: Multiple, parallel rows of sensilla.

label.value: proximal sensillum of ventral cibarial sense organ

value.value: Most proximal sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. It is innervated by two gustatory receptor neurons (Gendre et al., 2003).

label.value: distal sensillum of ventral cibarial sense organ

value.value: Distal-most sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. It is innervated by four gustatory receptor neurons (Gendre et al., 2003).

label.value: middle sensillum of ventral cibarial sense organ

value.value: Middle-most sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. It is innervated by 2 gustatory receptor neurons (Gendre et al., 2003).

label.value: ventral cibarial sense organ neuron of middle sensillum

value.value: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the middle sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. There are two of these per sensillum.

definition.value: Nayak & Singh (1983) claim the ventral cibarial sense organ is composed of two sensilla: the ventral and the dorsal sensilla. In contrast, Montell (2009), Vosshall & Stocker (2007), and Stocker & Schorderet (1981) report three sensilla: the proximal, the middle and the distal sensilla. This is shown via enhancer trap activity in Gendre et al., 1994. Similarly, the number of chemosensory neurons varies: both Nayak & Singh (1983), and Stocker (1994) report 6, whilst Gendre et al. (1994), Montell (2009), and Vosshall & Stocker (2007) report 8.

label.value: ventral cibarial sense organ neuron of distal sensillum

value.value: Gustatory receptor neuron that innervates the distal sensillum of the ventral cibarial sense organ of the adult pharynx. There are four of these per sensillum.

label.value: ventral row of cibarial sensilla

value.value: Cibarial bristle row that is ventral to the ventral cibarial sense organ in the adult pharynx. It consists of twelve to fifteen small bristles in the cibarium, each innervated by a single mechanoreceptor (Stocker and Schorderet, 1981; Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label.value: dorsal row of cibarial sensilla

value.value: Cibarial bristle row that is dorsal to the ventral cibarial sense organ in the adult pharynx. It consists of six to eight large bristles in the cibarium, each innervated by a single mechanosensory neuron (Stocker and Schorderet, 1981; Nayak and Singh, 1983).

label.value: adult pacemaker neuron

value.value: Pacemaker neuron that is part of the adult nervous system.

label.value: larval pacemaker neuron

value.value: Pacemaker neuron that is part of the larval nervous system.

label.value: pupal pacemaker neuron

value.value: Pacemaker neuron that is part of the pupa.

label.value: larval Pdf neuron

value.value: Larval neuron that expresses Pdf (FBgn0023178).

label.value: larval s-LNv Pdf neuron

value.value: Larval s-LNv neuron that expresses Pdf (FBgn0023178) from 4-5 hours after hatching and persists into adulthood (Helfrich-Forster, 1997). Its cell body is located close to the larval optic neuropil, into which dendritic fibers extend, spanning the distal and intermediate regions (Larderet et al., 2017). It projects to the superior lateral protocerebrum, where it has presynaptic terminals (Larderet et al., 2017). There are four of these cells per hemisphere.
